<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Brief memorandum on Public Attitudes to Climate Change, Nuclear Power and Energy Futures submitted to the DTI Energy Review 2006</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Dr Wouter Poortinga, Reader in Environmental Psychology, Welsh School of Architecture and School of Psychology, Cardiff University</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">BACKGROUND</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In this brief memorandum I will address a number of the questions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">set out in the call for evidence for the inquiry on the sustainability of measures to reduce the use of plastic shopping bags. I have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> expertise in environmental psychology, with a particular interest in sustainable lifestyles and behaviour</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> change, and led</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">study that evaluated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the introduction of the single-use carrier bag charge in Wales.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Over the past decade, many national, sub-national and local governments across the world have taken initiatives to reduce the sale or use of disposable plastic bags</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">These initiatives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have taken various shapes and form</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s, varying from an outright ban to the use of pricing instruments and voluntary measures.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">While anecdotal evidence suggests that many price-based initiatives have been successful in substantially reducing plastic bag use, not all of them have been systematically evaluated. Limited evidence is available in the academic literature regarding the relative effectiveness of different policy instruments (e.g. ban versus levy) and their attributes (e.g. size of the levy), as well as the long-term effectiveness and/or behavioural adaptations to a charge.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">We evaluated the effectiveness and further attitudinal and behavioural impacts of the single-use carrier bag charge that was introduced in Wales on October </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">2011. This was done by interviewing nationally representative quota samples before and after the introduction of the carrier bag charge in Wales. </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">England – </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">where no carrier bag charge was introduced at the time</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> of the study </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> served as </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> comparator</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">the ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS OF THE PROPOSED 5p CHARGE IN ENGLAND</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The proposed 5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> charge can be expected to substantially reduce the use of plastic bags in England. The available evidence on the effectiveness of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pricing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> instruments to reduce the use of plastic or other single-use carrier bags suggests that a reduction of 50 to 90% can be achieved</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the short term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The reduction in single-use carrier bag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in Wales was at the higher end of the spectrum. Data published by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waste &amp; Resources Action Programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (WRAP) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">shows </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that supermarket customers in Wales used 76% fewer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">single-use bags </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as compared to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 2011 when the single-use carrier bag charge was introduced. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Single-use carrier bag use by supermarket </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">customers in England</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increased by 4% over the same time period.</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The Welsh Government reports a 70-96% reduction </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">arrier bag usage in food retail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is evidence that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many shoppers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">easily </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">adapt to a carrier bag charge. Our study found that the number of consumers in Wales </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bringing their own bag to the supermarket ‘at their last visit’ increased from 62% before to 82% six months after the introduction of the charge. Our study </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">further </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">suggests that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘own bag use’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has become a habit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> many shoppers in Wales.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">While there is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">little</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> systematic evidence regarding the impacts of a plastic bag charge on the prevalence of littering, Ireland’s Litter Monitoring Body (200</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, 2005) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">show</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that the proportion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">plastic-bag litter dropped from 5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">prior to the introduction of the plastic bag levy to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 0.32% in 2002, 0.25% in 2003 and 0.22% in 2004.</span><a name="_ftnref10"></a><a href="#_ftn10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super"> </span><a name="_ftnref11"></a><a href="#_ftn11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref12"></a><a href="#_ftn12">[12]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Little is known about the long-term effectiveness </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a plastic bag charge. There is some evidence to suggest that a plastic bag levy needs to be increased after </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a number of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> years </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in order to retain its effectiveness</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. In Ireland, plastic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bag use started to increase</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> again</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> after the initial sharp drop in bag consumption. Plastic bag use decreased </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">once more</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> after the levy was raised in 2007.</span><a name="_ftnref13"></a><a href="#_ftn13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> In South Africa plastic bags use went up </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">two years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> after the introduction of the plastic bag levy in 2002. However, in South Africa the price of the plastic bag levy fell </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">substantially</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> three months after its introduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which could partly account for the observed increase in bag use</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref14"></a><a href="#_ftn14">[14]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our study shows that there is a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">majority </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(54%) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">support for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the introduction of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a si</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ngle-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">use carrier bag charge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in England</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. It can be expected that the charge will become more popular after it</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> introduc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In Wales, s</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">upport for the carrier bag charge was already high before it was introduced in 2011 (59%) and increased to 70% afterwards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Similar positive attitudinal changes were observed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> other environmental and behavioural change policies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The general public perceives a carrier bag charge to be an effective way of reducing waste and litter. Our study shows that the perceived effectiveness of the carrier bag charge to reduce waste and litter increased from 77% and 70% before to 79% and 76% after the introduction of the carrier bag charge in Wales.</span><a name="_ftnref15"></a><a href="#_ftn15">[15]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ANY WIDER ENVIRONMENTAL OR SUSTAINABILITY IMPLICATIONS OF A POSSIBLE INCREASED USE OF NATURAL-FIBRE ‘BAGS FOR LIFE’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our research examined </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">whether the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">re-usable bags could act as a ‘catalyst’ for further </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">waste-conscious </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">changes.</span><a name="_ftnref16"></a><a href="#_ftn16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> found </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">higher levels of a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">waste-conscious/environmental identity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">after the carrier bag charge was introduced in Wales, which may lead to other waste-conscious decisions in the longer term.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A plastic bag charge may have unintended environmental impacts if heavy-duty plastic bags </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that have replaced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> thin-gauge (single-use) plastic bags </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are not being</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> re-used and replaced as </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">intended. While an overwhelming majority of shoppers re-use </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">bags for life</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> at least once, there is some evidence that more heavy-duty plastic bags end up to landfill.</span><a name="_ftnref17"></a><a href="#_ftn17">[17]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">The environmental benefits of a plastic bag charge may be </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">diminished</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> if householders use purpose-made bin liners instead of re-using thin-gau</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">ge plastic carrier bags. Our</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> study found only a small reduction in the us</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">e of carrier bags as bin liners</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">14</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> More recent research reports that </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">the number of </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">Welsh householders using carrier bags</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> as bin liners</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> decreased </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">after the introduction of the carrier bag charge, </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">whilst </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">those</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> using purpose-made bin liners increased</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">17</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">While </span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt">unintended environmental impacts</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:11pt"> of the use of heavy-duty plastic bag and purpose-made bin liners instead of thin-gauge plastic bags need to be better understood, there are no indications that they negate the overall environmental benefits of a carrier bag charge.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">THE RELATIVE ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES OF THE PROPOSED LEVY RATHER THAN A COMPLETE BAN ON LIGHTWEIGHT PLASTIC BAGS</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Limited research has been conducted on the relative effectiveness of different policy instruments to reduce the use of plastic shopping bags. While own bag use rose sharply after the introduction of a complete ban in South Australia, a sizeable proportion of the shopping public still bought compostable single-use carrier bags.</span><a name="_ftnref18"></a><a href="#_ftn18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Overall, the impact of a complete ban on single-use carrier bag use appears to be of a similar size as that of a plastic bag charge.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is evidence that pricing instruments are more effective in reducing the use of single-use carrier bags than voluntary measures. Field experiments in which supermarket shoppers received ‘prompts’ or ‘persuasive normative messages’ established reductions in carrier bag use between about 20 and 40%.</span><a name="_ftnref19"></a><a href="#_ftn19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href="#_ftn20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_ftnref21"></a><a href="#_ftn21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">THE LESSONS TO BE LEARNT FRO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> OTHER COUNTRIES</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> EXPERIENCES IN THIS AREA</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Experiences from other countries show that e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ven </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a relatively small charge can produce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a substantial</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduction in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> plastic bag use</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1 </span><a name="_ftnref22"></a><a href="#_ftn22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> This suggests that a charge is not only to be understood as an economic instrument, but also as a ‘habit disruptor’ that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">forces </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">shoppers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to make a conscious decision as to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">whether they want to use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a plastic bag </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or not</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However, in the longer term a charge may need to be raised in order to retain its effectiveness. The few studies that have tracked carrier bag use over a longer period </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of time </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">suggest that bag use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may start</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to increase again</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> some</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> after the introduction of a charge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">13</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super"> 14</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Experiences from Wales show that real questions need to be asked about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unintended </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">consequences whereby heavy-duty ‘bags for life’ are being used as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">substitutes for single-use bags.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> This suggests that ‘bags for life’ need to be priced at an appropriate level to prevent such substitution effects.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">7</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our research suggests that a carrier bag charge is more acceptable if the proceeds of the charge is going to charity. A great majority in England (81%) is willing to pay a 5-pence charge if the money goes to charity.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">15</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">2 December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Poortinga, W., Whitmarsh, L., &amp; Suffolk, C. (2013). The introduction of a single-use carrier bag charge in Wales: Attitude change and behavioural spillover effects. Journal of Environmental Psychology, 36, 240-247.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Clapp, J., &amp; Swanston, L. (2009). Doing away with plastic shopping bags: international patterns of norm emergence and policy implementation. Environmental Politics, 18, 315-332.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> I use the terms “tax”, “levy” and “charge” interchangeably to refer to pricing instruments to reduce the use of ‘thin-gauge’ plastic or other single-use carrier bags. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Convery, F., McDonnell, S., &amp; Ferreira, S. (2007). The most popular 