t-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">prompt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> is a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> verbal, visual, written or recorded </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">cue that reminds people to carry out a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> specific</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> target behavio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">ur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> A ‘normative message’ is a verbal, visual, written or recorded communication that contains information about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">what types of behaviours are typically performed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">descriptive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">norms</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">), what types of behaviour </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">socially approved or disapproved of (injunctive norms), or that appeals to a personal moral obligation to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">engage in a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">particular</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> behaviour (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">personal norms).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Ohtomo, S., &amp; Ohnuma, S. (under review). Psychological interventional approach for reduce resource consumption: reducing plastic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">bag use at supermarkets. Document under review.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> De Groot, J.I.M., Abrahamse, W., &amp; Jones, K. (2013). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Persuasive normative messages: The influence of injunctive and personal norms on using free plastic bags. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Sustainability, 5, 1829-1844.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn22"></a><a href="#_ftnref22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> Homonoff, T. (2012). Can small incentives have large effects? The impact of taxes versus bonuses on disposable bag use. Job Market Paper</span><span style="font-family:'NewsGoth BT'; font-size:9pt">. Princeton: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">Department of Economics, Princeton University</span></p></body></html>